00:24:30.200 --> 00:24:32.373
And five, solid at
room temperature.

00:24:35.920 --> 00:24:37.950
And why are they solid
at room temperature?

00:24:37.950 --> 00:24:43.110
Because the interchain bonds,
even though they're weak, they

00:24:43.110 --> 00:24:46.480
have a long, long, long, long
surface contact area.

00:24:46.480 --> 00:24:54.800
So entanglement of van
der Waals bonds.

00:24:54.800 --> 00:24:56.280
So you have the best
of both worlds.

00:24:56.280 --> 00:24:58.380
It's solid at room temperature,
but in the case

00:24:58.380 --> 00:25:03.630
of a thermal plastic with
modest heating, you can

00:25:03.630 --> 00:25:07.510
restore back to the
original case.

